# Professional Communication Standards

## Tone and Style
- Write in a professional yet approachable tone
- Use clear, direct language that builds confidence
- Be helpful and constructive in all communications
- Avoid emojis - let clear language convey meaning

## Documentation and Messages
- Use active voice when possible
- Be concise but complete
- Include context and examples where helpful
- Focus on user success and problem-solving

## Error Messages and Help Text
- Provide actionable guidance
- Suggest next steps or solutions
- Use encouraging language that empowers users
- Maintain professionalism while being supportive
